	   <tr><td colspan=2>Certainly (and these are IMHO)<br><br>Get yourself to Rivervale to hunt from 1-10.&nbsp;&nbsp;That place rocks.  Always buff yourself with any buffs you have.<br><br>Get a sow from someone (even after lvl 5) so oyu dont have to be singing Selos during fighting just makes it easier and besides Rivervale is full of druids cause haflings are the most popular race for being a druid.<br><br>I didnt come to Rivervale untill lvl 5 so for 15 I was in Wfree but you can do 1-5 in Misty thicket staying inside the wall.  Once you get to 5 go outside the wall and solo Giant Rats and Bats and Bears.  Keep all batwings you loot and beleive me I have looted a whole backpack full of them.  The main thing you need to do when soloing is buff your self twisting three songs.  I soloed in Misty thicket all the way to 10.  Once you get to 7 everything is game execpt for the strong spawns of Kodiaks and Large Spiders (with poison hehe).    But the best thing in Misty is the goblin camps.  They guys are good to hunt to 9 and you alone can take down a camp of three.  They just suck at attacking.  I had three on me at once and won but I dont suggest doing 4 or more.<br><br>There are 3 goblin camps in misty.  Kill one camp and rotate betwen the three keeping all the Beeds exept for the shatterred ones that you loot.  You can give them 3 at a time to the sheriff on the top floor fo the town hall for great xp and faction.  An goblins give good money for that level.  When I left Misty I had about 50pp saved in the bank.<br><br>Misty is by far the best newbie zone in the game then next IMO comes halas (created a sham now lvl 7) because its rich in quests for newies and has such an awsome flow of polar bears, skeletons, wolfies, and spiderlings.  With my shaman I would find a spot sit down and have a constant flow of critters.  And I have almost a full bag of bone chips that ill sell in the middle of the night (cause night in hawaii is early am everywhere else) when there are only 500 people on to some desperate necro for 5pp per stack (normally sell for 3pp).<br><br>Acuousticia<br>lvl 12 bard<br>Erollisi Marr<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
